    "text255": "Operating System: The course is compatible with various operating systems, including Windows, macOS, and Linux. Ensure that your computer meets the minimum system requirements for running the required software and tools.",
    "text256": "Python Installation: You will need to install Python on your computer. The course will cover the installation process, so no prior installation is required. However, make sure you have the necessary permissions to install software on your computer or seek assistance if needed.",
    "text257": "Text Editor or Integrated Development Environment (IDE): Choose a text editor or IDE to write and edit your Python code. Popular options include Visual Studio Code, PyCharm, Sublime Text, or Atom. Select the one that suits your preferences and install it before starting the course.",
    "text258": "By meeting these requirements, you will be well-equipped to embark on the Education Course Details and gain a solid understanding of Python programming concepts.",
    "text259": "Gain the skills to handle food from start to finish in a safe and hygienic way",
    "text260": ">Hygiene is so important in food preparation. If caterers, chefs and wait staff are not adequately trained they can present huge health risks to the community.",
    "text261": ">On this course from the International Culinary Studio (ICS), you’ll learn why food safety matters and develop the confidence and skills to prepare and present food to the highest standards of hygiene and safety.",
    "text262": "Discover food safety procedures and the importance of both personal and workplace hygiene<",
    "text263": ">You’ll start by discussing the reasons for maintaining a high standard of food safety, such as food safety laws and reputation. Then, you’ll jump straight into what this means for you and how to implement processes to keep yourself and the working environment clean and hygienic.",
    "text264": "Learn the different categories of food poisoning and how to prevent them",
    "text265": ">One of the biggest risks of poor food hygiene is food poisoning. Not only is it bad for your business’ reputation but it can be very dangerous for your customers.",
    "text266": ">This course will guide you through the different types of food poisoning, what causes them, and how to prevent them. You’ll also look at hazardous foods as well as contamination in the kitchen.",
    "text267": "Explore food preparation and kitchen conduct in an ordinary and a COVID-19 environment",
    "text268": "Food safety and hygiene practices are easy to implement once you know how. This course will take you through all aspects of kitchen conduct including presentation in the kitchen, handwashing, and illness or injury.",
    "text269": "You’ll then learn the different ways that you can maintain a safe environment, from how to receive and store all types of food hygienically, to how to prepare, cook, hold, and serve food safely. This course will also cover COVID-19 and how the current pandemic affects food safety procedures.",
    "text270": "Gain an important life skill by learning how to cook tasty yet simple recipes",
    "text271": "Being able to cook is a fundamental skill that can turn meal preparation from a chore to a daily highlight.",
    "text272": "On this five-week course that’s fun for the whole family, you’ll cover the basics of cooking, from hygiene and kitchen safety procedures, to creating shopping lists and costing menus.",
    "text273": "Learn a variety of cooking methods and techniques with expert guidance from the International Culinary Studio<",
    "text274": "With leading educators in the culinary arts, you’ll discover how to confidently prepare different foods with ease. ",
    "text275": "You’ll be guided through the creative side of cooking, learning to combine tastes and flavours within dishes. The practical side of food preparation will also be explored, from creating shopping lists to costing a recipe.",
    "text276": "Using these skills, you’ll be able to manage food budgets, source ingredients, and create menus from scratch.",
    "text277": "Explore the fundamentals of food safety and hygiene",
    "text278": "When cooking, it’s important to maintain high levels of safety and hygiene at all times.",
    "text279": "You’ll examine how to dress appropriately for working in kitchens, hygiene basics, and the fundamentals of knife safety.",
    "text280": "With this knowledge, you’ll be able to prepare and serve food in a safe and hygienic environment and protect yourself from preventable accidents whilst cooking.",
    "text281": "Showcase your culinary skills by preparing eight easy recipes",
    "text282": "On this course, you’ll try your hand at a variety of sweet and savoury recipes that demonstrate a range of different techniques within an experienced cook’s repertoire.",
    "text283": "By the end of this course, you’ll have the skills to confidently prepare tasty meals to enjoy time and again. You’ll also have a foundational knowledge of the safety and hygiene procedures required to ensure professional standards of food preparation with every dish.",
    "text284": "THE MODERN WAY TO LEARN!",
